$$
\begin{array}{r l}
&{\mathrm{R}_{0}=\mathrm{G}\longrightarrow\mathrm{T}_{\mathrm{g}}\mathrm{G}+\beta\mathrm{G}\mathrm{T}_{\mathrm{p}}=\mathrm{G}(1\longrightarrow\mathrm{T}_{\mathrm{g}}+\beta\mathrm{T}_{\mathrm{p}})}\\
&{\mathrm{R}_{\mathrm{s}}=\mathrm{S}\longrightarrow\mathrm{T}_{\mathrm{p}}(\mathrm{S}\longrightarrow\mathrm{\ensuremath{\alpha}}\mathrm{\mathrm{S}})=\mathrm{S}[1\longrightarrow\mathrm{T}_{\mathrm{p}}(1\longrightarrow\mathrm{\ensuremath{\alpha}}\mathrm{\mathrm{a}})]}
\end{array}
$$

Here, G is the capital gain from stock options, S is the salary increment, Tₚ is the marginal personal income tax rate, T_g is the capital gains tax rate, β is the fraction of stock option gain adding to deductions, and a is the fraction of salary increment that is deductible.

